  "context_sent_to_llm": "Source [1]\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1).pdf\nSection: 3.2 PROJECT DELIVERY AND INSTALLATION\nPage: 2\n\nAs detailed in a SOW hereto, Developer will provide certain Services, Deliverables and Documentation to Client upon a designated Milestone in accordance with such Milestone's specific Specifications (collectively, Specific Specifications). Prior to completing a Milestone, Developer will: (a) inform Client of the availability of each portion of a Deliverable otherwise required be delivered by such Milestone date for testing by Client (he Acceptance Test Date)\u037e and (b) deliver to Client sue Deliverable (each a Milestone Deliverable) including the source code and object code form compatible with the platform(s) described in the SOW for such Milestone Deliverable.\n\nSource [2]\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1).pdf\nSection: 12.8 ENTIRE AGREEMENT AND UNDERSTANDING\nPage: 13\n\nThis Agreement and Appendices hereto are the complete and exclusive statement of agreement of the Parties as to matters covered by it. This Agreement and its Appendices replaces and supersedes all prior written or oral agreement or statements by and among the Parties with respect to the matters covered by it. This Agreement may not be modified or amended except in writing signed by a duly authorized representative of each Party.\n\nSource [3]\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1).pdf\nSection: 3.8 CLIENT ASSISTANCE\nPage: 3\n\nClient shall provide Developer assistance to complete the Services, and produce the Deliverables, as reasonably requested, including but not limited to providing the necessary information or documentation required from Developer for the development of the Subject Program. Client shall conduct all Acceptance Tests in good faith and shall not delay any acceptance of any Service or Deliverable without reasonable justification. The evaluation of any Service or Deliverable for any Acceptance Test will be based on material compliance with applicable Specifications and Client shall not arbitrarily withhold acceptance of any Milestone Deliverable or Subject Program.",
  "generated_answer": "**Comparison of Selected Documents**\n\nBased on the provided context, I will compare the selected documents on the following topics:\n\n* **Project Delivery and Installation**\n* **Entire Agreement and Understanding**\n* **Client Assistance**\n\n**Project Delivery and Installation**\n\n    **PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1)**\n    Developer will provide certain Services, Deliverables, and Documentation to Client upon a designated Milestone in accordance with such Milestone's specific Specifications.\n    Evidence: \"As detailed in a SOW hereto, Developer will provide certain Services, Deliverables and Documentation to Client upon a designated Milestone in accordance with such Milestone's specific Specifications (collectively, Specific Specifications).\" [Source [1]]\n\n    **Not specified**\n\n**Entire Agreement and Understanding**\n\n    **PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1)**\n    This Agreement and Appendices hereto are the complete and exclusive statement of agreement of the Parties as to matters covered by it.\n    Evidence: \"This Agreement and Appendices hereto are the complete and exclusive statement of agreement of the Parties as to matters covered by it.\" [Source [2]]\n\n    **Not specified**\n\n**Client Assistance**\n\n    **PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1)**\n    Client shall provide Developer assistance to complete the Services, and produce the Deliverables, as reasonably requested.\n    Evidence: \"Client shall provide Developer assistance to complete the Services, and produce the Deliverables, as reasonably requested, including but not limited to providing the necessary information or documentation required from Developer for the development of the Subject Program.\" [Source [3]]\n\n    **Not specified**",
